<item>
            <title>[SOLR-7420] Overseer stats are not reset on loss of ZK connection</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-7420</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Overseer stats are not reset when a node loses overseership due to a connection time out. If/when that node regains overseership in the future, statistics such as collection_operations/create/errors will resume from where they left off. If, in contrast, a node loses overseership due to a restart, those statistics reset to zero, so if/when that node regains overseership later on stats start from zero.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mewmewball&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mewmewball&quot;&gt;mewmewball&lt;/a&gt; for catching this one.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
